# Hospital Management System

## Business Requirement Document (BRD)

### Odoo Development Workshop Training Project

---

# 1. Introduction

## 1.1 Purpose

The purpose of this project is to develop a Hospital Management System using Odoo 13 that demonstrates all major Odoo development concepts covered during the Odoo Technical Development Workshop.

This project is not intended to be a complete hospital ERP. Instead, it serves as a practical learning project through which students will implement and understand Odoo development concepts such as:

* Models
* Fields
* Relationships
* Views
* Security
* Inheritance
* ORM
* Wizards
* Reports
* Dashboards
* APIs
* Chatter
* Webhooks

---

# 2. Business Problem

Hospitals manage:

* Doctors
* Patients
* Appointments
* Diseases
* Medicines
* Prescriptions

Most small hospitals manage this information manually using spreadsheets or paper files.

Management wants a centralized system to:

* Maintain patient records
* Maintain doctor records
* Schedule appointments
* Record prescriptions
* Track patient history
* Generate reports

---

# 3. Project Scope

The system shall provide the following modules:

## Master Data

* Departments
* Doctors
* Patients
* Disease Tags
* Medicines

## Transactions

* Appointments
* Prescriptions

## Reporting

* Patient Reports
* Doctor Reports
* Appointment Reports

## Analytics

* Graph Views
* Pivot Views
* Dashboards

## Administration

* User Roles
* Security
* Audit Trails

---

# 4. User Roles

## Receptionist

Responsibilities:

* Register Patients
* Schedule Appointments
* View Doctors
* Print Appointment Slips

Cannot:

* Delete Records
* Modify Prescriptions

---

## Doctor

Responsibilities:

* View Patients
* View Appointments
* Create Prescriptions
* Update Medical Notes

Cannot:

* Delete Patients

---

## Hospital Manager

Responsibilities:

* Full System Access
* Reports
* Analytics
* Dashboard Monitoring

---

# 5. Functional Requirements

# FR-01 Department Management

The system shall maintain hospital departments.

Examples:

* Cardiology
* Orthopedics
* ENT
* Internal Medicine
* Gastroenterology

Fields:

* Name
* Description

---

# FR-02 Doctor Management

The system shall maintain doctor profiles.

Fields:

* Doctor Code
* Name
* Email
* Mobile
* Department
* Specialization
* Active

Sample Records:

* Dr. Ahmad Badar
* Dr. Fahmina Ashfaq
* Dr. Umair Khurshid

---

# FR-03 Disease Tag Management

The system shall maintain disease categories.

Examples:

* Diabetes
* Hypertension
* Asthma
* Heart Disease
* Hepatitis

Fields:

* Name
* Color

Purpose:

Used for patient categorization.

---

# FR-04 Medicine Management

The system shall maintain medicines.

Fields:

* Code
* Name
* Price

Examples:

* Paracetamol
* Augmentin
* Metformin
* Losartan

---

# FR-05 Patient Registration

The system shall allow registration of patients.

Fields:

* Patient Reference
* Name
* Gender
* Date of Birth
* Mobile
* Email
* Blood Group
* Guardian Name
* Assigned Doctor
* Disease Tags

---

# FR-06 Automatic Patient Number

The system shall automatically generate patient references.

Example:

PAT00001

PAT00002

PAT00003

Implementation:

* Sequence
* create() Override

---

# FR-07 Appointment Management

The system shall allow scheduling appointments.

Fields:

* Appointment Number
* Patient
* Doctor
* Date
* Time
* Status

Statuses:

* Draft
* Confirmed
* Completed
* Cancelled

---

# FR-08 Prescription Management

The system shall allow doctors to prescribe medicines.

Fields:

* Prescription Number
* Patient
* Doctor
* Date

Lines:

* Medicine
* Quantity
* Unit Price

Relationship:

Prescription → One2many → Prescription Lines

---

# FR-09 Patient Medical History

The system shall maintain historical records.

Users should be able to view:

* Appointments
* Prescriptions
* Disease Tags

for a patient.

---

# FR-10 Dashboard

Management shall view:

* Total Patients
* Total Doctors
* Total Appointments
* Completed Appointments

through Graph and Pivot Views.

---

# 6. Non-Functional Requirements

## Security

Receptionists shall not delete patients.

Doctors shall only manage medical records.

Managers shall have complete access.

---

## Auditability

Patient changes shall be tracked using:

* mail.thread
* tracking=True

---

## Performance

The system shall support:

* 10 Doctors
* 25 Patients
* 50 Medicines
* 1000 Appointments

without performance issues.

---

# 7. Odoo Concepts Covered

| Requirement    | Odoo Concept       |
| -------------- | ------------------ |
| Departments    | Simple Model       |
| Doctors        | Many2one           |
| Disease Tags   | Many2many          |
| Medicines      | Master Data        |
| Patients       | Computed Fields    |
| Appointments   | Workflow States    |
| Prescriptions  | One2many           |
| Patient Number | Sequence           |
| Security       | ACL + Record Rules |
| Dashboard      | Graph + Pivot      |
| Reports        | QWeb               |
| Chatter        | mail.thread        |
| Bulk Assign    | Wizard             |
| APIs           | Controller         |
| Analytics      | ORM read_group     |

---

# 8. Demo Dataset

The training database shall include:

* 8 Departments
* 10 Doctors
* 25 Patients
* 15 Disease Tags
* 50 Medicines
* 50 Appointments
* 25 Prescriptions

to demonstrate all workshop features.

---

# 9. Expected Learning Outcome

After completing this project, students shall be able to:

1. Gather requirements.
2. Design database models.
3. Create Odoo modules.
4. Develop views.
5. Configure security.
6. Implement business logic.
7. Generate reports.
8. Build dashboards.
9. Create APIs.
10. Deploy Odoo applications.

The student should understand how a real-world business requirement is transformed into a working Odoo module.
